description: Barcode Professional for Silverlight generates high quality vector-based Linear, Postal, MICR, Composite and 2D Symbologies. Features: - Linear & 2D Barcodes - Silverlight printing and data-binding support, raster image exportation (WriteableBitmap), Barcode rotation (0, 90, 180, 270 degrees), Silverlight Out-of-Browser Applications support - Full design-time support Visual Studio 2010, Visual Studio Express Editions (Visual Basic, Visual C#), Expression Blend . Supported Barcode Symbologies - Australia Post 4-state Barcode, ABC Codabar, USS Code 128 A-B-C, USS Code 39, USS Code 93, Data Matrix ECC200, Deutsche Post Identcode, Deutsche Post Leitcode, EAN-13, GTIN-13, EAN-8, GTIN-8, EAN-99, Coupon Barcode, EAN-Velocity, Industrial 2 of 5, Standard 2 of 5, Interleaved 2 of 5, ITF 25, ISBN, Bookland EAN, ISBN-13, ISBN-10, ISMN, ISSN, ITF-14, EAN-14, DUN-14, GTIN-14, JAN-13, JAN-8, MSI, OPC, PDF417, Portable Data File 417, PDF417 Truncated, PLANET, POSTNET, PZN, British Royal Mail 4-State Customer Barcode, RM4SCC, Royal TPG Post KIX 4-State Barcode, SCC-14, Singapore 4-State Postal Code Barcode, SSCC-18, UPC-128, EAN-18, Swiss PostParcel Barcode, UCC-EAN-128, EAN-128, GTIN-128, UPC-A, UPC-E, GTIN-12, USPS Sack Label, USPS Tray Label Barcode, QR Code, USPS FIM, USPS Horizontal Bars, Telepen, Pharmacode, Semacode, Code 32 Italian Pharmacode IMH, USPS Package Identification Code (PIC), FedEx Ground 96, HIBC LIC/PAS, ISBT 128, Italian Post 25, USPS Intelligent Mail Barcode, VICS BOL, VICS Bill of Lading, VICS SCAC PRO, Aztec Code, Compact PDF417, Macro PDF417, Micro PDF417, Micro QR Code, UPS MaxiCode, GS1 DataBar, RSS-14, Matrix 2 of 5, Danish Postal 39, French Postal 39 A/R, GS1 DataMatrix, MICR E-13-B, ALL EAN.UCC Composite Barcodes CC-A, CC-B, CC-C, USPS Intelligent Mail Container Barcode, USPS IMpb, USPS Zip+4
releaseNotes:
# Fixed! A bug in the Auto encoding algorithm for Data Matrix 2D symbology
# Fixed! A bug in the Auto encoding algorithm for QR Code 2D symbology
# New! Added USPS Intelligent Mail Package Barcode (IMpb) new format to the UspsPicUccEan128 symbology. It does support the three primary “channels” or payment categories i.e. Commercial, Online, and Retail. The new IMpb accepts 5-digit and 9-digit codes (USPS Zip+4).
summary: Add High-Quality Vector-based barcodes to Silverlight LOB projects. It supports Linear (1D), Postal, Composite and 2D Symbologies. For SL4 and SL5.
title: Silverlight Barcode Pro
